escape-coding.blurb: search for escape codes in the entropy coding stage for slightly better compression

hard-resync.blurb: Perform clipping and sample flushing upon discontinuity

mark-granule.blurb: Apply granule semantics to buffer metadata (implies perfect-timestamp)

max-lpc-order.blurb: Max LPC order; 0 => use only fixed predictors

max-residual-partition-order.blurb: Max residual partition order (above 4 doesn't usually help much)

mid-side-stereo.blurb: Do mid side stereo (only for stereo input)

min-residual-partition-order.blurb: Min residual partition order (above 4 doesn't usually help much)

padding.blurb: Write a PADDING block with this length in bytes

perfect-timestamp.blurb: Favour perfect timestamps over tracking upstream timestamps

qlp-coeff-prec-search.blurb: false = use qlp_coeff_precision, true = search around qlp_coeff_precision, take best

qlp-coeff-precision.blurb: Precision in bits of quantized linear-predictor coefficients; 0 = automatic

rice-parameter-search-dist.blurb: 0 = try only calc'd parameter k; else try all [k-dist..k+dist] parameters, use best

seekpoints.blurb: Add SEEKTABLE metadata (if > 0, number of entries, if < 0, interval in sec)

streamable-subset.blurb: true to limit encoder to generating a Subset stream, else false

reserved-prefill.blurb: Prefill samples table of reserved duration

reset-muxer.blurb: Reset the muxer after each segment. Disabling this will not work for most muxers.

send-keyframe-requests.blurb: Request a keyframe every max-size-time ns to try splitting at that point. Needs max-size-bytes to be 0 in order to be effective.

sink.blurb: The sink element (or element chain) to use (NULL = default filesink). Valid only for async-finalize = FALSE

sink-factory.blurb: The sink element factory to use (default = filesink). Valid only for async-finalize = TRUE

sink-properties.blurb: The sink element properties to use. Example: {properties,boolean-prop=true,string-prop="hi"}. Valid only for async-finalize = TRUE

use-robust-muxing.blurb: Check if muxers support robust muxing via the reserved-max-duration and reserved-duration-remaining properties and use them if so. (Only present on qtmux and mp4mux for now). splitmuxsink may then also  create new fragments if the reserved header space is about to overflow. Note that for mp4mux and qtmux, reserved-moov-update-period must be set manually by the app to a non-zero value for robust muxing to have an effect.
